# Chess vs AI - Tkinter Python Game

A simple **Chess game built with Python and Tkinter**, where you can play as White against a basic AI that makes random moves. The game uses **python-chess** for chess rules and logic, and **Pillow** for displaying piece images.

---

## Features

- Play as White against an AI opponent.
- Click-to-select and move pieces.
- Highlights the selected piece.
- Pawn promotion automatically handled (promotes to Queen).
- Simple AI that plays random legal moves.
- Tkinter GUI with chess board and piece images.

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.10+  
- [Tkinter](https://docs.python.org/3/library/tkinter.html) (usually comes with Python)  
- [python-chess](https://pypi.org/project/python-chess/)  
- [Pillow](https://pypi.org/project/Pillow/)  

---

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:

```bash
git clone 
cd <repo-folder>

### Create and activate a virtual environment (recommended):

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Linux/macOS
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows

## Install dependencies:
pip install python-chess pillow

# Make sure you have an images/ folder in the project directory with the 12 chess pieces named as:
r,n,b,q,k,p,R,N,B,Q,K,P.png

### Running the Game ###
python chesser.py
